name: app.R
content:
library(shiny)
library(ape)
library(Biostrings)
library(ggtree)
library(phangorn)  # For additional tree methods like FastME

# Define UI for the app
ui <- fluidPage(
  titlePanel("Phylogenetic Tree Viewer"),
  
  sidebarLayout(
    sidebarPanel(
      fileInput("fasta_file", "Upload FASTA File", accept = c(".fasta", ".fa", ".faa")),
      
      selectInput("tree_method", "Select Tree Construction Method:",
                  choices = c("Neighbor-Joining (NJ)" = "nj",
                              "UPGMA" = "upgma",
                              "FastME Balanced" = "fastme_bal",
                              "FastME OLS" = "fastme_ols")),
      
      actionButton("generate_tree", "Generate Phylogenetic Tree"),
      hr(),
      helpText("Upload a FASTA file and choose a tree construction method to generate the phylogenetic tree.")
    ),
    
    # UI
    mainPanel(
      tabsetPanel(
        tabPanel("APE Tree Visualization",
                 plotOutput("ape_tree_plot", height = "600px")  # Increase height
        ),
        tabPanel("GGTREE Visualization",
                 plotOutput("ggtree_plot", height = "600px")  # Consistent height
        )
      )
    )
  )
)

# Define server logic
server <- function(input, output, session) {
  tree_data <- reactiveVal(NULL)  # Store the tree data
  
  observeEvent(input$generate_tree, {
    req(input$fasta_file)  # Ensure file is uploaded
    
    # Read the uploaded FASTA file
    fasta_path <- input$fasta_file$datapath
    sequences <- readDNAStringSet(fasta_path)
    
    # Convert sequences to DNAbin format for distance calculation
    dna_bin <- as.DNAbin(sequences)
    
    # Compute pairwise distance matrix
    dist_matrix <- dist.dna(dna_bin, model = "raw", pairwise.deletion = TRUE)
    
    # Choose tree construction method based on dropdown input
    tree_method <- input$tree_method
    
    if (tree_method == "nj") {
      tree <- nj(dist_matrix)  # Neighbor-Joining
    } else if (tree_method == "upgma") {
      tree <- upgma(dist_matrix)  # UPGMA
    } else if (tree_method == "fastme_bal") {
      tree <- fastme.bal(dist_matrix, nni = TRUE, spr = TRUE)  # FastME Balanced
    } else if (tree_method == "fastme_ols") {
      tree <- fastme.ols(dist_matrix, nni = TRUE, spr = TRUE)  # FastME OLS
    }
    
    tree_data(tree)  # Save the tree
  })
  
  # APE Tree Plot
  output$ape_tree_plot <- renderPlot({
    req(tree_data())
    
    # Ladderize the tree for cleaner visualization
    ladderized_tree <- ladderize(tree_data())
    
    # Calculate dynamic vertical limits
    num_tips <- length(ladderized_tree$tip.label)
    vertical_space <- num_tips * 1.2  # Adjust multiplier for more space
    
    # Plot the tree with expanded ylim
    plot.phylo(ladderized_tree, 
               main = paste("Phylogenetic Tree (", input$tree_method, ")", sep = ""),
               cex = 0.8,                # Adjust tip label size
               y.lim = c(0, vertical_space),  # Add dynamic vertical spacing
               no.margin = FALSE)        # Avoid automatic margin cropping
  })
  
  
  
  # GGTREE Visualization
  output$ggtree_plot <- renderPlot({
    req(tree_data())
    
    # Generate the ggtree plot and set a title with the ggplot2 framework
    ggtree(tree_data()) + 
      geom_tiplab() +
      #xlim(-1,20)+
      theme_tree2() +
      theme(plot.margin = unit(c(14,8,14,8), "mm")) +  # Add some padding
      ggplot2::labs(title = paste("Phylogenetic Tree (", input$tree_method, ")", sep = ""))
  })
  
  
}

# Run the application
shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)
